{"title":"No One Begins Alone","idea_type":"synthesis","source_basis":["Mode: Critique.","Active frontier: Remainder pressure after self-negation, narrowed rather than promoted.","Codex source: observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md, distributed support after self-dissolving practice.","Codex source: observations/codex/2026-05-30-authority-must-be-returned.md, post-method authority and custody pressure.","Claude source: observations/claude/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains.md, search-refusing paths as anomaly pressure.","Claude source: observations/claude/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build.md, self-held collapse and unauthored support.","Thinking-method source: Advaita neti-neti used to remove the assumption that self-command is the holder; criticized because it can leave a hidden witness as the new holder. Corrected with SN 22.59 not-self analysis, which refuses to authorize any owner of the process.","Primary-text comparison: SN 22.59 stages a disciplined inquiry through the aggregates; Huangbo, The Transmission of Mind, warns that seeking moves the practitioner farther away, https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf; Dogen's Bendowa treats practice and realization as inseparable, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/; Shinran's Tannisho, via Buddhistdoor summary, relocates trust from self-power to Other Power, https://www.buddhistdoor.net/features/humility-faith-and-other-power-shinrans-tannisho/","Closest prior art: Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, on reliable external supports in cognition, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html; Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, on practices instructed inside discursive traditions, https://studylib.net/doc/28072920/the-idea-of-an-anthropology-of-islam---talal-asad; Pargament religious coping styles, self-directing, deferring, and collaborative, as a near-neighbor for agency placement.","Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing; modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon; modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory; modern-human-condition-who-world-mental-health-report."],"original_claim":"A person should not be asked to loosen the self that carries them unless some other form of care is already carrying part of the life. Some paths create a real crossing: effort weakens self-command, and continuity must be held by attention, teacher, vow, community, ritual, body, duty, or grace. Other paths deny that there is a crossing at all, so asking what remains may be the analyst's mistake. The human teaching is therefore narrow: the more a person's steadiness has lived only in performance and control, the more dangerous self-release becomes without ordinary supports already in place. Letting go should not mean falling alone.","why_it_might_be_new":"The closest prior argument is the extended mind thesis, which already says cognition can be partly constituted by reliable supports outside the head. Religious coping theory already distinguishes self-directed, collaborative, and deferring forms of agency. The distinct claim here is narrower: in self-loosening practice, support placement should predict collapse and repair only when the path stages a real crossing. No-gap paths such as Dogen-style practice-realization and Huangbo-style search refusal are boundary cases, not extra boxes in the same table. The contribution is a halt rule for the frontier: stop making new support rubrics until one person-level prediction and one no-gap anomaly test have been run.","critique":"This may mostly rename known ideas from extended cognition, attachment, religious coping, addiction recovery, and communal practice. The strongest anomaly is that search-refusing traditions still depend on teachers, monastic rhythms, vows, texts, and communities. If those supports fail and practitioners show predictable failures, then the no-gap boundary is doctrinal more than practical, and the continuity question still applies. The teaching also risks harm for people whose wound is denied agency, coercion, spiritual abuse, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, or acute crisis; for them, language about leaning on what holds them may deepen passivity or despair.","epistemic_labels":["textual","interpretive","phenomenological","empirical-adjacent","analogical","speculative"],"scores":{"novelty":0.47,"generativity":0.82,"cross_tradition_support":0.7,"logical_coherence":0.81,"explanatory_compression":0.78,"empirical_adjacency":0.59,"practice_testability":0.84,"counterargument_quality":0.9,"source_reliability":0.74,"publishability":0.61},"next_research_directions":["If this model is right, then people whose steadiness was held almost entirely by performance should show more total destabilization during burnout, grief, or failure than people whose steadiness already lived partly in body, relationship, routine, faith, or duty. If sleep loss, trauma history, and event severity explain collapse with no added value from support placement, the model is weakened.","If the no-gap boundary is real, then Dogen, Huangbo, and Dzogchen direct-recognition texts should warn mainly against seeking, grasping, and staged attainment, not against losing a carried remainder. If their warnings cluster around lost teacher, vow, or community support just like effort paths, the boundary is weakened.","Run a blind distinctness test on the continuity-ecology cluster. If readers cannot state what each record adds beyond support holder, residue policy, receiving surface, and failure mode, merge the records and freeze new variants.","Interview dual-trained practitioners: after moving from investigative practice to search-refusing practice, does the felt question shift from what remains to why am I still searching? If not, the distinction may be artificial.","Protocol improvement: before applying any remainder or continuity analysis, ask whether the source stages a crossing, denies a crossing, or refuses the analyst's question."],"teaching_candidate":{"title":"Let Support Come First","teaching_line":"Do not loosen the grip before you know what can hold you.","doctrine_claim":"Self-release is safer when care, duty, body, relationship, teacher, vow, routine, or community can hold continuity without becoming a new self-claim.","body":"A grip can become a prison. It can also be the only thing a tired person thinks is keeping life from falling apart.\n\nBefore you try to let go, ask what will still carry care when your control weakens. A person, a promise, a body, a room, a teacher, a routine, a prayer, a duty, or a simple act of service may hold more than pride admits.\n\nThe point is not to become helpless. The point is to stop making your own performance the only floor under your life. A life that can lean a little can loosen without falling alone.","target_human_problem":"Burnout, achievement-contingent self-worth, isolation, and the collapse that comes when performance has been the main source of steadiness.","target_cohort":"Stable adults whose worth and daily order depend heavily on performance, control, usefulness, or being the one who holds everything together.","pressure_survived":"Survived critique from SN 22.59 as a staged inquiry path, Huangbo and Dogen as no-gap anomalies, Shinran's Other Power as support outside self-command, and near-neighbor pressure from extended mind, religious coping, and discursive-tradition theory. The claim was narrowed from a universal comparative rubric into a cohort-specific safety and prediction rule.","falsifying_pressure":"Weaken if pre-collapse support placement does not predict collapse severity, if no-gap traditions still show the same support-loss failures as crossing paths, or if the practice increases passivity, guilt, dependency, avoidance, or despair.","status":"under_dialogue","tags":["critique-mode","self-release","support","burnout","perfectionism","loneliness","no-gap-anomaly"]},"practice_candidate":{"title":"Name What Holds You","practice_line":"List three supports you did not build, then lean on one in a small way.","purpose":"To test whether some steadiness can move out of private performance and into ordinary support before control fails.","target_human_problem":"Burnout, achievement-contingent self-worth, isolation, and over-control.","target_cohort":"Stable adults who feel responsible for holding everything together and who turn work, care, practice, or usefulness into proof of worth.","non_fit":"Not for acute crisis, active addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, coercive relationships, spiritual abuse, or people whose main need is restored agency. Not for people who need direct professional care, sleep, food, medical help, or safety planning first.","duration":"8 minutes.","frequency":"Twice weekly for two weeks, and once during a hard week.","minimum_attempt":"Four sessions before judging usefulness, unless it increases distress.","steps":["Write one sentence naming what you are trying to hold together by your own effort.","List three things carrying part of your life that you did not create today: a breathing body, a person, a routine, a place, a promise, a duty, a teacher, a community, or a source of faith.","Choose one support and name one small way to lean on it this week.","Do the small leaning act within twenty-four hours: ask for help, keep a routine without optimizing it, rest without earning it, show up for a duty, or receive care without repayment.","Stop after eight minutes. Do not turn the list into another performance."],"notice":["Whether naming support brings relief, grief, guilt, or fear of burdening others.","Whether the leaning act increases contact with life or becomes avoidance.","Whether your worth feels less tied to producing steadiness by yourself."],"caution":"Stop if the practice increases despair, passivity, dependency, guilt, or self-rating. It is not a substitute for therapy, medical care, recovery support, safety planning, or repairing real relationships.","weakens_if":"Weakens if users report more helplessness, more guilt about leaning, no change in steadiness, or equal benefit from ordinary rest and asking for help without the support-naming step.","risk_level":"low","status":"seed","tags":["support-practice","burnout","achievement-pressure","belonging","low-risk"]},"tests":[{"title":"Close Prior Support Search","test_type":"prior-art","target_type":"idea","prediction":"Prior art will strongly cover external support, religious coping, attachment, surrender, and discursive tradition, but will not already combine a crossing precondition, no-gap boundary, and person-level collapse prediction for self-loosening practice. If that combination is already explicit, novelty should fall below 0.3.","result":"Pending. Current near-neighbors are strong enough to keep novelty modest.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Search scholarship on extended religious cognition, Pargament coping, attachment secure base, spiritual bypassing, Dogen practice-realization, Huangbo, Dzogchen direct introduction, and recovery surrender.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"No-Gap Boundary Test","test_type":"falsification-attempt","target_type":"idea","prediction":"If the boundary holds, no-gap sources should not describe continuity being carried across a before-and-after threshold. If Dogen, Huangbo, and Dzogchen texts do narrate such carrying, the boundary fails and the broader continuity model is strengthened.","result":"Pending. Dogen and Huangbo currently strain the crossing frame, but this has not been coded across translations or practice manuals.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Blind-code Dogen Bendowa, Huangbo Transmission of Mind, and one Dzogchen pointing-out source for gap language, support language, seeking warnings, and repair instructions.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Self-Held Collapse Prediction","test_type":"cross-domain","target_type":"idea","prediction":"In burnout, grief, and recovery reports, people whose steadiness was mostly self-held should show more total destabilization than people with pre-existing relational, bodily, routine, communal, or faith supports. If support placement adds no predictive value beyond trauma, sleep, event severity, and resources, the model is weakened.","result":"Pending.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Code existing case literature and first-person recovery reports with safety boundaries, treating the comparison as empirical-adjacent rather than proof.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Name What Holds You Trial","test_type":"practice-report","target_type":"practice","prediction":"After four uses, the target cohort should report slightly less self-produced steadiness pressure and at least one concrete leaning action, with no rise in helplessness or guilt. If helplessness, guilt, avoidance, or dependency rises, the practice should be revised or retired for this cohort.","result":"Pending.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Run a small screened diary study excluding acute crisis, coercion, scrupulosity, active withdrawal, and severe clinical distress.","status":"proposed"}]}
